        <num>CCRP 498</num>
        <heading>498.  Copy of indictment or information</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 498.  Copy of indictment or information
A certified copy of the indictment or information shall be furnished by the clerk of court to a defendant upon his request.  Failure to furnish a correct copy of the indictment or information shall not affect the validity of the criminal prosecution, unless the defendant was substantially prejudiced thereby.</p>
        </content>
